criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Are diagnosed with Parkinson's disease;

          -  That they are classified between I III on the Hoehn & Yahr motor staging scale;

          -  Men who score greater than 21.1 seconds for the dominant limb and 22.3 seconds for the
             non-dominant limb for the nine-hole peg test.

          -  Women who scored greater than 19.9 seconds for the dominant limb and 21.4 seconds for
             the non-dominant limb for the nine-hole peg test.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Have a brain pacemaker implant;

          -  Have recent injuries or limitations that make it impossible for the upper limbs to
             function;

          -  Do not perform/abstain from two visits out of the 16 proposed in the intervention
             protocol regardless of the group that will be allocated.
